						               													<description>Open Field Battle is a simple wargame portraying generic 17th-century combat; no specific battle is represented.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has a force of pikemen, cavalry, musketeers, and cannons. Each turn a player gets a random number of command points to spend on musketeers and cannons firing and on pikemen and cavalry moving and assaulting.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Combat is deterministic; the result depends on the formation the defender is in and the status of the defender and any neighboring units. E.g., a lone defender or one at the end of a line is disrupted (or eliminated if already disrupted), but one with two undisrupted neighbors merely retreats. The neighboring units may suffer effects as well.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Optional rules allow for different ways of using the command points and the possibility of saving them from turn to turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
